  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-10-08",
    "date": "2021-11-24T17:49:06Z",
    "text": "Primary and Virtual Care Affordability Act\n\nThis bill extends until December 31, 2023, the exemption for telehealth services from certain high deductible health plan rules. It also provides a high deductible health plan safe harbor for the absence of a deductible for certain primary care services provided in any plan year beginning on or before December 31, 2023 (COVID-19 emergency period).\n\nThe Government Accountability Office must complete a study, and report on, the effects of the safe harbor for certain primary care services provided during the COVID-19 emergency period."
  },
